ls and articulate resources/capacities needed to achieve these goals</p>', 'KES.200,000 to KES.300,000', 'null', 'Kenya', 'Nairobi', 'cc@staffscout.co.ke', 2, 'null', 1, '<p>Citywise is looking for a resourceful and ambitious Manager - Partnering with Cities with experience in program<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ndesign, project management, urban development and/or qualitative/quantitative research. The role will entail<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ndeveloping strategy and plans, developing proposals, building relationships with partners, and managing a portfolio of<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nprojects. A key focus in 2022 will be to support the startup of our work on SWASSA to ensure the timely<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nimplementation of an ambitious Year 2 work plan for the design and pilot testing of a container-based, full-value<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nchain sanitation service in Bukavu, DRC. This leader will create a strategy to grow our portfolio in alignment with<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nthe company&#39;s values and objectives, while adapting to meet practical requirements of partnering with municipalities and bi/multilateral funding institutions.</p>', '2022-01-26 17:33:33', '2022-01-26 17:33:33', '2022-02-02', 0),
(16, 197, 7, 96, 6, 6, 1, 'Advisory Services Manager', 1, '4-7', 'Senior Level', '<p>● 5 years of work experience, preferably in a project-based and client-facing industry<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Master&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field or comparable experience<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Strong written and verbal communication skills in English<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Familiarity with challenges of urban development, and interest - if not experience - in safely managed sanitation<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Demonstrated ability to inspire, motivate and develop team members to deliver exceptional work and<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ngrow professionally - teams you lead consistently deliver on expectations, and teammates you manage take on<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nincreasing responsibility over time<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Recognized ability to prioritize and maintain a birds-eye view of multiple projects - you know how to create<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nand maintain the tools/systems you need to ensure your team delivers on-time<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Commitment to excellence - you know what constitutes a phenomenal deliverable - from rigorous analysis,<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nevidence-based conclusions and practical recommendations to consistent formatting and professional<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\npresentation - and you pride yourself on consistently delivering phenomenal work<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Relevant, contextualized, quantitative analysis - you have exceptional skills in structuring and conducting<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nanalyses to answer complicated, ambiguous questions and you have a track record of figuring out how to adapt<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nand interpret within a real-world (often resource-constrained) context.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Ability to work toward established big-picture goals with minimal supervision - you thrive when the end goal<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nis established, but the route is undefined. When presented with a challenge and not given clear instructions on<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nhow to solve it, you confidently deliver a proposal that is sufficiently developed such that collaborators can<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nunderstand the approach and expected result in order to give meaningful feedback<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Excitement to iterate collaboratively - you&rsquo;re not discouraged when your sufficiently developed proposal is met<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nwith lots of feedback; you like to create a first draft to get peoples&rsquo; wheels turning and enjoy leading a group to a<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nfinished product by independently to incorporating feedback in between collaborative sessions</p>', '<p><strong>Strategy Development</strong><br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Develop strategy for growth of Citywise&rsquo;s project portfolio, including setting growth targets and identifying ideal<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nprojects and partners to meet organizational objectives<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Review and refine Citywise&rsquo;s project pricing strategy<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Review and refine approach to staffing projects, balancing priorities of efficiency, cost-effectiveness, and internal<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ncapacity development<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nBusiness Development<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Build pipeline of projects by monitoring formal opportunities and developing relationships with potential partners,<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nand take lead on conceptualizing projects, in collaboration with Director<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Develop proposals, including budgets, and iterate with clients to finalize project scope<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Collaborate with Operations Manager to execute contracts that clearly document shared expectations<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,var(--tw-bg-opacity)); letter-spacing: 0.025em;\">Project Management and Delivery</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>● Manage end-to-end implementation and delivery of advisory services<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Manage direct reports and external consultants to complete deliverables<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Manage all active and potential projects simultaneously to ensure on-time fulfillment of commitments<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Hold ultimate responsibility for exceptional quality of all deliverables<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Collaborate with Operations Manager to facilitate invoicing and payment</p>', 'KES.200,000 to KES. 300,000', 'null', 'Kenya', 'Nairobi', 'cc@staffscout.co.ke', 2, 'null', 1, '<p>We are looking for an ambitious strategist with skills in people and project management to manage and grow our<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nportfolio of global sanitation advisory projects. The role will entail developing strategy and plans, developing<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nproposals, building relationships with clients, and managing a portfolio of projects. Since our inception in 2018, we<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nhave intentionally maintained a broad interpretation of our objective of building capacity of and momentum for the sector through developing leaders, creating tools, and sharing best practices to increase the likelihood of success of cities&#39; adoption of citywide inclusive sanitation. We have taken on engagements with a variety of customer types, including governments, universities, private corporations, and international NGOs in this initial stage of market exploration. As we move into the next stage, the Manager - Citywise Advisory Services will develop the strategy for scaling the impact of Citywise. This leader will create a high-level strategy and 3-year strategic plan for growing our portfolio and optimizing the way we deliver our services - while maintaining our record of delivering exceptional results for our clients, in part through our &ldquo;special sauce&rdquo; as an advisor with an implementer&rsquo;s mindset and experience.</p>', '2022-01-26 17:55:05', '2022-01-26 17:55:05', '2022-02-02', 0),
(17, 197, 8, 96, 6, 6, 1, 'General Manager - Kisumu', 1, '4-7', 'Senior Level', '<p>&bull; 5+ years&rsquo; experience in operations, corporate leadership, managing people and budgets<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Strong experience in developing and executing on a business strategy<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Commercial acumen with proven ability to create opportunities for growth within an organization<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Demonstrated ability to build concrete and sustained operational partnerships with government<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Demonstrated experience in managing county wide teams with diverse professional development<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nneeds<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Critical and analytical thinking skills; ability to work with both large and limited amounts of data to<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ndevelop strategy and make rigorous decisions<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Highly organized with a high capacity to problem solve and establish priorities for self and team<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Ability to inspire confidence and instill trust both internally and externally<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Strong negotiator, with a proven ability to secure new opportunities or gain the best deal<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Proven success in building strong and effective people centric teams<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Demonstrated passion for the organization&rsquo;s mission, values and customers<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Excited about driving impact at scale and portfolio growth<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Impeccable integrity and ethics</p>', '<p><strong>Strategy &amp; Planning</strong><br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nContinuously build insight into our business model, market position, broader climate, risks, and<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nopportunities so that Fresh Life can successfully navigate towards our goal of serving urban areas<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nthroughout Kenya<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nCraft a clear and inspiring strategy with support from the Managing Director and drive implementation to<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nserve 100,000 people across Kisumu with inclusive and high-quality non-sewered sanitation services by<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n2026</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n<strong>Execution</strong><br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Set annual objectives that directly tie to achieving our 5-year strategic goals, communicate them<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nthroughout the organization to guide our work year to year, and drive execution by building a culture<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nand processes for recognition and accountability<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Spearhead the delivery of impactful initiatives, implementing continuous improvements for service<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nenhancement at county office levels and ensure that key performance indicators are met<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Inspire the team to keep work moving forward by balancing competing priorities, making effective<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ndecisions, and generating innovative ideas</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n<strong>Government &amp; External Relations</strong><br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Build long term, trusting relationships with crucial external stakeholders, particularly government<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\npartners, that enable our operations and strategy to succeed<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Secure formal partnerships and contracts with utilities, as well as the county government in<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\norder to expand and sustain our operations<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Be the face of Fresh Life in Kisumu and represent our brand to enhance our ability to achieve our<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nmission<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Actively network by using existing and newly established connections to build and enhance<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nFresh Life&rsquo;s public profile at events, conferences, and speaking engagements<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nLeadership, People, and Culture<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Model leadership behaviors and our values to build a positive, thriving team culture that enables a<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nrapidly growing, high-performing team of 100 to succeed<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Build an effective organizational structure that both empowers and nurtures a culture of<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\naccountability so that we are executing towards our goals<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Develop and coach a team of leaders empowered to lead strategy, people, and implementation<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nin each of their domains towards shared goals</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n<strong>Organizational Operations</strong><br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Steer the financial health of the Kisumu office, including driving financial planning and<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nanalysis, forecasting, and financial and administrative operational excellence<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n&bull; Develop and maintain KPIs and targets for all direct reports and business units, and oversee the accountability and accomplishment of each target set</p>', 'KES.200,000 to KES.400,000', 'null', 'Kenya', 'Nairobi', 'cc@staffscout.co.ke', 2, 'null', 1, '<p>We are looking for a visionary General Manager -Kisumu of Fresh Life, our sanitation innovation<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ncompany, who will lead an exceptional, mission-driven team and guide our strategy and operations in Kisumu.</p>', '2022-01-26 18:12:05', '2022-01-26 18:12:05', '2022-02-02', 0),
(18, 197, 7, 96, 6, 5, 1, 'Senior Strategy Associate', 1, '4-7', 'Mid Level', '<p>● Bachelor&rsquo;s degree, with 3+ years of relevant work experience in industries requiring a high level of<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nquantitative and analytical skills<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Exceptional analytical (qualitative and quantitative), structured problem solving, and communication skills<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Prior experience working with large data sets and excel-based analytical modeling<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Prior experience in planning and executing qualitative research (e.g., user research)<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Ability to independently operate with high levels of ambiguity, with a passion for getting things done and<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nimproving processes<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Ability to autonomously lead projects by multitasking, setting and executing on priorities, and<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ncoordinating with senior internal and external stakeholders<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● High level of proficiency in Microsoft Office, particularly Excel, PowerPoint and Word and Google Suites</p>', '<p>● Work directly with the Head of the Strategic Projects team and in close coordination with the senior<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nleadership team to take on complex and critical cross-cutting strategy projects<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Identify new revenue generating initiatives and evaluate potential based on profitability, feasibility, and<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nopportunity for scale<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Pilot and operationalize opportunities to optimize revenue streams through existing channels and/or new<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nchannels and through partnerships<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Drive improvements in customer experience by combining quantitative data with a deep understanding<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nof user needs, habits, and perceptions developed through targeted interviews, usability studies, and<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ncustomer feedback<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Support development of framework and analysis to determine market expansion priorities, identify<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nengagement strategies, and develop plans for partnership building and implementation<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● In close collaboration with Sales, Customer Support, Credit, Logistics, New Products &amp; Services, and<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nFinance, design and implement tests that generate the necessary data to make strategic decisions about<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nFresh Life&rsquo;s organizational growth</p>', 'KES.300.000', 'null', 'Kenya', 'Nairobi', 'cc@staffscout.co.ke', 2, 'null', 1, '<p>We are seeking to hire a Senior Strategy Associate to join the Strategic Projects team. Fresh Life&rsquo;s network has<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ngrown rapidly, and we now serve over 120,000 people in Nairobi with plans to scale to 750,000 people in Nairobi and 500,000 people in new geographies by 2025. Through our product and service offerings, we are currently able to provide safe sanitation at 25% of the annualized cost to provide safe sanitation using sewers. We now aim to bring the cost/person/year to $0, through a combination of gained cost efficiencies and the identification of new revenue streams.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nThe Strategic Projects team is Fresh Life&rsquo;s internal strategy and consulting function, responsible for:<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Optimizing the business model for existing products and services<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Expanding the business model to new geographies both within Kenya and internationally<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Developing strategic partnerships that aid in #1 and #2 as well as help Fresh Life to explore adjacent<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nproducts and services</p>', '2022-01-26 18:18:46', '2022-01-26 18:18:46', '2022-02-02', 0),
(19, 197, 11, 84, 6, 6, 1, 'Head of Maintenance', 1, '8-12', 'Mid Level', '<p>● Bachelor&#39;s degree in Engineering.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Advanced degree preferred<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● 5+ years of managerial experience.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● 5+ years of experience in maintenance operations.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Knowledge of Total Productive Maintenance (TPM) and Reliability Centered Maintenance (RCM) will be preferred<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Strong knowledge of facilities, machines and equipment.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Excellent organizational and leadership abilities.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills.</p>', '<p>● Structure the maintenance team to ensure quick resolution of breakdowns, so as to achieve a reduced mean time to repair (MTTR)<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Design and lead the implementation of a reliability program to increase mean time between failure (MTBF).<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nLeverage on TPM and or RCM methodologies to design an effective program.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Custodian of the maintenance budget. Lead maintenance cost improvement projects.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Create and implement maintenance procedures<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Ensure the maintenance team adhere to safety policies and procedures<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Set up structures to manage engineering spares.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Design and implement a maintenance dashboard that should be used to drive accountability within the&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; maintenance teams. Track metrics such as Uptime, MTTR, MTBF, Costs due to recurrent issues, adherence to<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nthe agreed turnaround time, costs of PM (Preventive Maintenance), costs of BM (Breakdown Maintenance) and<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nrun projects to improve performance and reduce costs<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Set up a learning and development framework for operators, technical operators and technicians to ensure that<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nequipment is used and maintained as per the set standards.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Set up systems to continuously improve the condition and maintenance of assets by addressing root causes,<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nand by mitigating/controlling failure modes and their effects</p>', 'KES.250,000', 'null', 'Kenya', 'Kinanie, Athi River', 'cc@staffscout.co.ke', 2, 'null', 1, '<p>We are looking for a mission-driven&nbsp;Head of Maintenance to oversee the maintenance and reliability team to<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nensure equipment and facilities are efficiently and effectively used and maintained across all the company factories in Kenya.</p>', '2022-02-10 19:28:37', '2022-02-10 19:28:37', '2022-02-21', 0);
INSERT INTO `jobs` (`id`, `user_id`, `specialism_id`, `industry_id`, `contract_type_id`, `education_level_id`, `experience_id`, `jobs_title`, `search_and_listing`, `experience_length`, `experience_level`, `qualifications_competencies`, `duties_responsibilities`, `offered_salary`, `address`, `country`, `city`, `email`, `gender`, `languages`, `is_active`, `jobs_description`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `application_deadline`, `is_company_name_hidden`) VALUES
(20, 197, 5, 121, 6, 5, 1, 'Senior Software Engineer', 1, '4-7', 'Mid Level', '<p>● Degree in Computer Science/IT preferred<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● At least 3-4 years of FullStack development experience<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Vast working knowledge and experience of Python, Node.js React, AWS, Django<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Experience in building and deploying Android/Java Apps<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Experience taking software projects through the entire software lifecycle (requirements analysis, design,<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nimplementation, deployment, post deployment support)<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Development and support of systems that are critical to the day to day operations of medium and large<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\norganizations (ERPs, financial systems, CRMs, MRPs etc)<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Demonstrable knowledge and experience with professional software development practices and tools including<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nsource code control, defect tracking, unit testing and code reviews.</p>', '<p>● To design innovative new systems, tools and processes that significantly improve operations throughout the<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\norganization; ensuring that IT solutions developed provide optimal solutions to the problems they solve.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Developing standards and guidelines for software design and coding to be used by the software team.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Ensuring that our IT systems will scale in line with the overall organization growth strategy.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Leading of software development resources (in-house and contracted) on architecture improvement projects;<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ncustomizing internal systems with off the shelf software.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Determining all of the sub-tasks required to successfully implement the agreed upon solution, to spec and on<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ntime.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Responsible for diagnosing problems in development, and coming up with several solution options for both the<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nshort-term and the long-term.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Responsible for using formal de-bugging methods to identify the root-cause of issues, and implement a<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ncorrective action plan based on the analysis done of a best-fit solution.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Responsible for recommending best-fit solutions, languages, and frameworks for all web and Android projects.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Work with managers to set clear KPIs (quarterly and annually) and ensure work aligns to these goals/metrics and<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ncome prepared with documentation for quarterly review meetings with managers<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Perform code reviews to identify opportunities for future enhancement to code written/apps developed.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Work closely with vendors to ensure projects move forward and stay on time and ensure that services are<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nworking as expected and promised, and raise concerns to mgmt if otherwise.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Manage fellows, partner school students and grads, Unvi interns and grads<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● As the Scrum master you&rsquo;ll be responsible for facilitating daily scrum for developers, reporting updates to daily<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nstaff meetings, sprint planning, sprint demo and retrospective meetings.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Responsible for planning all deployment schedules, project roadmap timelines, appropriately assessing potential<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nrisks/timeline slips and making ongoing adjustments to task prioritization as needed.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Supporting in-house users of our custom software and problem solving.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Provide mentorship and general knowledge transfer in matters IT related to members of the IT team.</p>', 'KES.250,000', 'null', 'Kenya', 'Nairobi', 'cc@staffscout.co.ke', 2, 'null', 1, '<p>The Senior Software Engineer will lead the development of custom enterprise software to power and improve the<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nefficiency of our rigorous processes across the network in line with the overall organization growth strategy</p>', '2022-02-23 15:49:23', '2022-02-23 15:49:23', '2022-03-02', 0),
(21, 197, 13, 121, 6, 5, 1, 'Finance and Regulatory Specialist', 1, '8-12', 'Mid Level', '<p>● 5 to 10 years of work experience in research &amp; analysis in the areas of law and financing (financing for<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\ngovernment projects a preferred specialization)<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Vast experience in Public Private Partnerships</p>\r\n\r\n<p>● Demonstrated understanding of regulatory reform work<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Demonstrated understanding of national and county budgeting processes<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Demonstrated understanding of the WASH sector in Kenya<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Strong connections to relevant government stakeholders<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● A Master&rsquo;s Degree in Finance Law (or a related degree)<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● A self-starter who is motivated to conduct research without supervision<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Highly organized team player, with proactive and flexible work style.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Language: English required. Fluency in French or Swahili is a plus.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Humility, integrity and a sense of humour.</p>', '<p>● Develop and deploy a strategy to work closely with relevant government stakeholders to increase the<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nprioritization of national and county budgeting in WASH and sanitation.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Work with the system to become involved in the budget-making process in Kenya.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Build capacity of government and other relevant stakeholders on the importance of increased financing reform to shape future growth of sector know how.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Develop recommended financing structures and mechanisms &ndash; with hard numbers to back up the ideas! &ndash; to<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\npromote government investment in serving low&ndash;income areas with sanitation.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Develop and deploy a strategy to work closely with relevant government stakeholders to strengthen the<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nregulatory environment such that non&ndash;sewered sanitation is recognized and measurable.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Build capacity of government and other relevant stakeholders on the importance of regulatory reform to shape<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nfuture growth of the sector.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Maintain existing relationships with key government stakeholders including identifying opportunities to grow the partnerships<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Provide strategic research and analysis to inform plans for expansion of services<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Develop recommended metrics for stakeholder analysis and uptake.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Coordinate, prepare, or review regulatory submissions for projects.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Maintain current knowledge base of existing and emerging regulations, standards, or guidance documents.<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\n● Interpret regulatory rules or rule changes and ensure that the company stays aligned with regulatory rules.</p>', 'KES.300,000', 'null', 'Kenya', 'Nairobi', 'cc@staffscout.co.ke', 2, 'null', 1, '<p>StaffScout&nbsp;is looking for an exceptional individual who seeks to transform Kenya by joining the&nbsp;Government Affairs and Policy team. The Finance &amp; Regulatory Specialist will examine and analyse the fiscal and regulatory regime in<br role=\"presentation\" />\r\nKenya as well as other countries in which the company&nbsp;plans to expand or support local partners in expanding sanitation services, and then will fight for regulatory and financial reform in the sector. Together with other teams within the company, the Finance &amp; Regulatory Specialist will establish strategies as to how the current fiscal and regulatory regimes could be amended within the legal jurisdiction. The Finance &amp; Regulatory Specialist will also support Government Departments through technical support &amp; policy amendment to sustainably improve finance regimes.</p>', '2022-02-23 16:03:29', '2022-02-23 16:03:29', '2022-03-02', 0),
(22, 197, 5, 337, 6, 5, 1, 'Product Manager', 1, '4-7', 'Mid Level', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Degree in Computer Science/Software Engineering/Computing/Business Related fields.</li>\r\n	<li>Experience taking software projects through the entire software life-cycle (requirements analysis, design, implementation, deployment, post deployment support).</li>\r\n	<li>Strong experience in a dynamic software product management role with proven experience overseeing all elements of the product development lifecycle.</li>\r\n	<li>Previous software and web development experience and highly effective at working with cross-functional teams.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Analyse our end-users&rsquo; needs, current market trends, and potential partnerships from an ROI and build vs. buy perspective</li>\r\n	<li>Analyse current and future product requirements and develop appropriate implementation programs and production timelines to ensure they&rsquo;re successful achieved</li>\r\n	<li>Appraise new product ideas, end-user requests and feature requirements, and strategise appropriate implementation plans</li>\r\n	<li>Translate software application product strategy into detailed requirements for prototype construction and final product development by Development team</li>\r\n	<li>Responsible for the QA processes for the Software Applications and working closely with end users to drive adoption</li>\r\n	<li>Responsible for managing the project implementation and release schedules for the software products and keeping the end-users apprised of status. You will be the designated team&rsquo;s Scrum Master for the Software Development Sprints</li>\r\n	<li>Supervise a team of Analysts and work with the development team to support prioritise feature releases and ensure that they understand the specifications.</li>\r\n	<li>Support in the Quality Assurance and Testing and documentation of features for the Production Environment</li>\r\n</ul>', 'KES.100,000', 'null', 'Kenya', 'Nairobi', 'cc@staffscout.co.ke', 2, 'null', 1, '<p>We are hiring a <b>Product Manager</b> to join the IT team. You will work alongside developers and report directly to the General Manager - IT. To succeed in this role you will have a keen eye for gaps in our product offerings and the innovative mindset to fill them. You are a highly skilled analyst with a proven ability to strategize the full lifecycle of enterprise software products production &mdash; from conception through release and to subsequent continuous product improvement.</p>', '2022-03-21 14:16:26', '2022-03-21 16:39:47', '2022-03-28', 0);
